title: Accrington Stanley 3-4 AFC Wimbledon: Match Report
text:
Accrington Stanley 3-4 AFC Wimbledon: Match Report 20 Oct 2015 21:31:00 
comments AFC Wimbledon fight back to win seven-goal thriller against Accrington StanleyLyle Taylor and Dannie Bulman both scored twice as AFC Wimbledon recorded a pulsating 4-3 win over promotion-chasing Accrington Stanley.The Reds got off to a dream start on five minutes when a Sean McConville free-kick hit the wall, came back out to the winger who clipped the ball back in and Billy Kee got ahead of his marker to slot home.And Kee doubled up on 10 minutes when McConville's free-kick from the right was headed home by the striker.However, Wimbledon got one back on 19 minutes when, from a long throw, the ball was only cleared to Dannie Bulman on the edge of the area and he rifled it home.And it was level on 25 minutes when George Francomb's cross was slotted home by Taylor from around 12 yards.In a breathtaking game, Stanley went back ahead on 36 minutes following a quick passing move with Terry Gornell finding McConville who drilled the ball into the roof of the net.But once again the Dons came back on 44 minutes with Bulman claiming his second of the match, Taylor finding him 20 yards out and he fired low into the back of the net.Taylor scored the winning goal on 64 minutes when he got the ball in the area from Barry Fuller and turned and found the far corner.
